<p><it>d</it>. = defective year; <it>d.l</it>. = defective leap year;
<it>p.</it> = perfect year; <it>p.l.</it> = perfect leap year;
<it>r.</it> = regular year; <it>r.l.</it> = regular leap
year.⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p></note>

